            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An RTO parcel is refused or undelivered and comes back without the customer ever taking possession, so no sale should be recognised on it at all. A customer return is a delivered order sent back later and is recorded as a sales return through a credit note. RTO also carries both forward and return freight with no revenue against it."
